HGV Video Productions, Inc. was a Canadian home video company that was formed in 1989 as the Canadian branch of Anchor Bay Entertainment, formerly Video Treasures and GoodTimes Entertainment. Its headquarters were located in Ajax, Ontario. It distributed children's material such as Thomas the Tank Engine and HIT Entertainment's Beatrix Potter films, as well as horror films like Troll and fitness video releases. In August 2002, the company was renamed to Anchor Bay Canada and was later folded into its parent company.
